{
  "stem": "4700.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, life was quite difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, people tried to emigrate, but again, that was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a rumor that you can get a visa to A, so people queued at that consulate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They obtained the visa but they couldn't get the transit visas because you had to go by train through other countries, which refused to give you transit visas.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or you got a transit visa and then the final visa already expired.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a very difficult time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Also people who wanted to go to America or somewhere by boat-- well, it was very difficult to secure a birth.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was a state of panic everywhere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "People just trying to escape, not knowing what, but they knew things were going to be bad.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[SIGHS] And the people who couldn't escape-- they just lived as well as they could and tried to exist from day to day.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then the worst thing was when the transport started in '41.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Prior to that, they send Polish-- former Polish citizens, people who were born in Poland and emigrated to Czechoslovakia after World War I-- they were sent back to Poland I think much earlier, either in '39 or '40.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But somehow we didn't-- it didn't touch us so much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because we were, after all, Czech Jews and this couldn't happen to us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then the deportation started and we-- 5,000 people were sent to Lodz and to the Lodz ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then, and in November '41, Theresienstadt was founded.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the transport started to go to Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were hopeful that it will be the camp for Czech Jews and that we stay there for the duration of the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
